    <compoundname>md__c_1_2programation_2ulaval_2_g_a_u_l_2programmation_2_t_a_g_c_a_n_2guide__utilisation_203___d_o_n_n_e_e_s___c_a_n</compoundname>
    <title>03 - Manipulation du Buffer de Données CAN</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><anchor id="md__c_1_2programation_2ulaval_2_g_a_u_l_2programmation_2_t_a_g_c_a_n_2guide__utilisation_203___d_o_n_n_e_e_s___c_a_n_1autotoc_md66"/></para>
<sect1 id="md__c_1_2programation_2ulaval_2_g_a_u_l_2programmation_2_t_a_g_c_a_n_2guide__utilisation_203___d_o_n_n_e_e_s___c_a_n_1autotoc_md67">
<title>Objectif</title><para>Comprendre comment gérer le buffer de données CAN (<computeroutput><ref refid="com__utils_8h_1af553c31425b32bd9c020380c942ed3bd" kindref="member">TxData</ref></computeroutput> et <computeroutput><ref refid="com__utils_8c_1a14629afcc7f0b2d62c2b617b07d98184" kindref="member">RxData</ref></computeroutput>) au-delà de la simple interface des tags.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="md__c_1_2programation_2ulaval_2_g_a_u_l_2programmation_2_t_a_g_c_a_n_2guide__utilisation_203___d_o_n_n_e_e_s___c_a_n_1autotoc_md69">
<title>Structure du buffer CAN</title><sect2 id="md__c_1_2programation_2ulaval_2_g_a_u_l_2programmation_2_t_a_g_c_a_n_2guide__utilisation_203___d_o_n_n_e_e_s___c_a_n_1autotoc_md70">
<title>Taille et format</title><para><programlisting filename=".c"><codeline><highlight class="normal">uint8_t<sp/><ref refid="com__utils_8h_1af553c31425b32bd9c020380c942ed3bd" kindref="member">TxData</ref>[8];<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>Buffer<sp/>de<sp/>transmission<sp/>(8<sp/>octets<sp/>=<sp/>CAN<sp/>standard)</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">uint8_t<sp/><ref refid="com__utils_8c_1a14629afcc7f0b2d62c2b617b07d98184" kindref="member">RxData</ref>[8];<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>Buffer<sp/>de<sp/>réception<sp/>(8<sp/>octets)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Le buffer CAN est toujours de <bold>8 octets</bold> (64 bits) pour un frame standard CAN.</para>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="md__c_1_2programation_2ulaval_2_g_a_u_l_2programmation_2_t_a_g_c_a_n_2guide__utilisation_203___d_o_n_n_e_e_s___c_a_n_1autotoc_md71">
<title>Hiérarchie</title><para><table rows="5" cols="3"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Niveau  </para>
</entry><entry thead="yes"><para>Composant  </para>
</entry><entry thead="yes"><para>Responsabilité  </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><bold>Haut</bold>  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Application  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Appelle <computeroutput><ref refid="data__container_8h_1aa84538f1ab0c319056787e9674157405" kindref="member">set_value()</ref></computeroutput>, <computeroutput><ref refid="data__container_8h_1a66cbaaa79a2ba3c2c7912514c1dc805f" kindref="member">get_value()</ref></computeroutput>  </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><bold>Moyen</bold>  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Data Container (TAGCAN)  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Mappe les tags dans le buffer  </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><bold>Bas</bold>  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Buffer <computeroutput><ref refid="com__utils_8h_1af553c31425b32bd9c020380c942ed3bd" kindref="member">TxData</ref>[8]</computeroutput> / <computeroutput><ref refid="com__utils_8c_1a14629afcc7f0b2d62c2b617b07d98184" kindref="member">RxData</ref>[8]</computeroutput>  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Storiage binaire brut  </para>
</entry></row>
